    hadithEnglish:
      'It was narrated from Jabir bin Abdullah that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:\n&ldquo;Cover your vessels, tie your water skins, extinguish your lamps and lock your doors, for Satan does not untie a water skin, open a door or uncover a vessel. If a person cannot find anything but a stick with which to cover his vessel and mention the Name of Allah, then let him do so. And the mouse could set fire to the house with its people inside.&rdquo;',
