    hadithEnglish:
      'It was narrated from Abdul-Jabbar bin Wail that :\nhis father said: I prayed with the Prophet (ﷺ) and a man said: Alhamdu lillahi hamdan kathiran tayyiban mubarakan fihi (Praise is to Allah, much, good and blessed praise). When the Prophet (ﷺ) finished praying, he said: Who said that? The man said: It was me, but I did not mean anything but good. He said: The gates of heaven were opened because of it and nothing prevented it from reaching the Throne.',
