      'It was narrated from Abu Dharr that :\nthe Messenger of Allah (saas) said: Allah, the Blessed and Exalted, said: Whoever does one good deed will have (the reward of) ten like it and more, and whoever does a bad deed will have one like it, or I will forgive him. Whoever draws near to Me a hand span, I draw near to him an arms length; whoever comes to Me a forearms length, I draw near him an arms length; whoever comes to Me walking, I come to him in a hurry. Whoever meets Me with an earthful of sins, but does not associate anything in worship with Me, I will meet it (i.e., his sins) with forgiveness equal to that.',
