      'Abu Hurairah told that the Messenger of Allah (saas) said:\nAllahumma! Inni audhu bika minal-arba: min ilmin la yanfau, wa min qalbin la yakhshau, wa min nafsin la tashbau, wa min duain la yusma [O Allah, I seek refuge with You from four things: From knowledge that is of no benefit, from a heart that does not fear (You), from a soul that is never satisfied, and from a supplication that is not heard].',
