      'Aishah narrated that when the Prophet (ﷺ) saw a cloud approaching from any horizon, he would stop what he was doing, even if he was praying, and turn to face it, then he would say:\n&ldquo;Allahumma inna naudhu bika min sharri ma ursila bihi (O Allah, we seek refuge with You from the evil of that with which it is sent).&rdquo; Then if it rained he would say: &ldquo;Allahumma sayyiban nafian (O Allah, a beneficial rain),&rdquo; two or three times. And if Allah dispelled it and it did not rain, he would praise Allah for that.',
