      'It was narrated that Abu Hurairah met a woman who was wearing perfume and heading for the mosque. He said:\n&ldquo;O slavewoman of the Compeller, where are you headed?&rdquo; She said: &ldquo;To the mosque.&rdquo; He said: &ldquo;And have you put on perfume for that?&rdquo; She said: &ldquo;Yes.&rdquo; He said: &ldquo;I heard the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) say: Any woman who puts on perfume then goes out to the mosque, no prayer will be accepted from her until she takes a bath.&rdquo;',
