    hadithEnglish:
      'It was narrated from Ibn Masud that a man came to the Prophet (ﷺ) and said that he had kissed a woman, and he started to ask about expiation, but he (the Prophet (ﷺ)) did not say anything to him. Then Allah revealed the Verse:\n&ldquo;And perform prayers at the two ends of the day and in some hours of the night. Verily, the good deeds remove the evil deeds. That is a reminder for the mindful.&rdquo; [11:114] The man said: &ldquo;O Messenger of Allah, is this (the Verse) just for me?&rdquo; He said: &ldquo;It is for whoever acts upon it among my nation.&rdquo;',
