      'It was narrated from Anas that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:\n&ldquo;None of you should wish for death because of some harm that befalls him. If he must wish for death, let him say: O Allah, keep me alive so long as living is good for me and cause me to die when death is good for me.&rdquo;',
