    hadithEnglish:
      'It was narrated from Anas bin Malik that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:\n&ldquo;On the Day of Resurrection the disbeliever who lived the most luxurious will be brought, and it will be said: Dip him once in Hell. So he will be dipped in it, then it will be said to him: O so- and-so, have you every enjoyed any pleasure? He will say: No, I have never enjoyed any pleasure. Then the believer who suffered the most hardship and trouble will be brought and it will be said: Dip him once in Paradise. So he will be dipped in it and it will be said to him: O so-and-so, have you ever suffered any hardship or trouble? He will say: I have never suffered any hardship or trouble.&rdquo;',
